title: For Sale:  Sako AI Vixen .223rem; EARLY- '79-'81, VERY NICE!
postcontent: For sale is a gorgeous Sako AI Vixen rifle chambered in .223 Remington. This gun has obviously been fired very little, and has only very minor handling marks. I'm not an official grader of guns, but I would not hesitate to say that the bluing is at least 98%. This is an all-original collectible shooter, equipped with the original 1" dovetail rings, all ready for your favorite scope. The gun is also equipped with a very nice leather sling.The AI Stamped Sako's were made from 1979-1992, and according to the Sako website, this particular gun is one of the earliest ones made, with a serial number dating it back to the 1979-81 range. This is before ANY changes were made from the original design of this model rifle. Later on they made a few changes, but this one is the old style that isn't too easy to find anymore.Like I said, everything about this gun is simply fantastic. The only handling marks I've noticed are a few small, very light scratches in the high-gloss finish, and the tiniest bit of bluing wear on the bolt handle. I did my best to sow the gun very well in my pictures. If you have any questions or requests for more pictures, just ask, and I will respond to you asap. These guns, which you already know if you know Sako's at all, are absolutely incredible shooters, and if you want to use it for more than just paper targets, it's lightweight-but-strong build, amazingly smooth action and pinpoint accuracy make it one of the finest long-range hunting guns out there!Local face-to-face transactions are always enjoyable, but if you live a distance away and it needs to be shipped, I'm ok with that, too.  Shipping is $35 to the Continental US, or $60 to Hawaii or Alaska. Insurance is optional for the buyer, and will cost an additional $20 upon buyer's request. I accept USPS money orders only for payment.My return policy for shipped guns is this: If the buyer finds that the gun has been falsely advertised, then DO NOT complete the FFL transfer. Instead, have your FFL ship it back to my FFL within 3 days of receiving it, and the full payment will be returned to buyer immediately, minus any shipping and FFL fees that have been incurred, given that the gun comes back to me in the same condition that I sent it. There will be no returns allowed if an FFL transfer has been completed, so please inspect your gun thoroughly BEFORE you decide to make the transfer. I sell my guns with great confidence, and therefore I do not expect that the buyer will want to return it, but just in case, I do like to offer my buyers an opportunity to return a purchase based on their assessment of the accuracy of my advertisement. If you want to be more confident in your purchase, you can find this gun for sale under the same title on GB, and I welcome you to read any of my buyer feedbacks, all of which are A+ feedbacks, thankfully.Thanks for checking out this beautiful gun.  If you are interested, I look forward to hearing from you soon.  You can either email me through this sight or text me at REDACTED.  Thanks again.  God bless.
